      Anti-ESG
   =20
 =20
We  talked yesterday about an assumption in a lot of environmental, social =
and governance investing, which is that you shouldn=E2=80=99t invest in soc=
ially bad things because eventually they will be regulated out of existence=
. Buying oil-company stock, on this theory, is=C2=A0financially risky, beca=
use eventually world governments will crack down on oil drilling, and the o=
il companies will not be able to drill for oil profitably in the long run. =
Eventually a company=E2=80=99s externalities =E2=80=94=C2=A0pollution, soci=
al harms, etc. =E2=80=94=C2=A0will have to be internalized; shareholders wi=
ll ultimately have to bear the costs that the company imposes on society.I =
am skeptical about this assumption, without thinking that it matters too mu=
ch in practice. I wrote:Do you think that world governments will come toget=
her to ban or limit oil drilling to limit=C2=A0climate change? Do you think=
 governments will regulate Facebook in a way that harms Facebook, or that u=
sers will flee over the most recent controversies? I dunno, maybe, but my t=
endency is to bet on inaction in these areas.But does it matter? If all the=
 shareholders of all the oil companies go to them and say =E2=80=9Cfind a w=
ay to stop drilling oil because eventually there will be laws against it,=
=E2=80=9D and the oil companies do what the shareholders want and pivot awa=
y from oil, and new oil projects can=E2=80=99t get financed because investo=
rs all think that they are not viable in the long run, then the problem is =
solved,=C2=A0even if governments never actually pass laws against it.=C2=A0=
On the other hand  here=E2=80=99s this:Wall Street=E2=80=99s three biggest =
municipal-bond underwriters have seen business grind to a halt in Texas aft=
er the state blocked governments from working with banks that have curtaile=
d gun-industry ties. In June, as Goldman Sachs Group Inc. was on the hunt f=
or a new campus in Dallas, Republican Governor Greg Abbott took a shot at E=
SG initiatives by banning state investments in businesses that cut ties wit=
h oil and gas companies.Not only has Texas not taken steps to limit oil and=
 gas drilling, it has taken steps to make it illegal=C2=A0not=C2=A0to suppo=
rt oil and gas drilling. If your theory of ESG investing is =E2=80=9Cwe hav=
e to divest from fossil fuels because ultimately regulators will ban them,=
=E2=80=9D it has to feel a little weird when the regulators instead=C2=A0ba=
n divesting from fossil fuels.
