      Don=E2=80=99t put it in email
   =20
 =20
An occasional theme around here is that if you are doing crimes you should =
not memorialize them in permanent searchable written electronic communicati=
ons. If you want to  manipulate Libor, walk over to the Libor submitter and=
 say =E2=80=9Chey I=E2=80=99ll buy you a case of champagne if you make Libo=
r too high=E2=80=9D; don=E2=80=99t say that in email or a Bloomberg chat. T=
his is also true if you are in the Mafia and the crime you are committing i=
s extortion:A new generation of wiseguys didn=E2=80=99t properly learn the =
business, according to former government investigators. Older members compl=
ain that the millennials=E2=80=94who grew up in the suburbs instead of city=
 streets=E2=80=94are softer, dumber and not as loyal as mobsters of the pas=
t. Plus, they=E2=80=99re always texting.=E2=80=9CEverything is on the phone=
s with them,=E2=80=9D said a former made member of the Colombo family who k=
nows some of the men accused in the case. One Colombo associate is accused =
of sending threatening texts to a union official over extortion collections=
.=E2=80=9CHey this is the 2nd text, there isnt going to be a 3rd,=E2=80=9D =
the associate wrote, according to court records.=E2=80=9CI am sure that is =
frowned upon in mob circles,=E2=80=9D former FBI agent and crisis-managemen=
t consultant Richard Frankel said of what appeared to be incriminating text=
s.Frowned upon in any circles! First of all you have created excellent evid=
ence for prosecutors at your extortion trial, but also, is this threat=C2=
=A0effective? If you show up at a guy=E2=80=99s office with a baseball bat =
and say =E2=80=9Cthis is your second warning, there won=E2=80=99t be a thir=
d,=E2=80=9D you get your point across. The baseball bat suffices to explain=
 what will happen instead of a third warning. =E2=80=9CIf you don=E2=80=99t=
 give us the money I will stop texting you=E2=80=9D is just strictly not a =
threat at all =E2=80=94=C2=A0who doesn=E2=80=99t want you to stop texting? =
=E2=80=94=C2=A0and you=E2=80=99re not there with a baseball bat to make the=
 implicit threat clear. I guess that=E2=80=99s the defense at trial. =E2=80=
=9CNo, that text wasn=E2=80=99t a threat, that was just an opt-out message,=
 what I meant by that was =E2=80=98Please give us our money, or text STOP t=
o opt out of these texts.=E2=80=99=E2=80=9D
