olid; background-color: #ccc;"> talked yesterday</a> about an assumption in=
 a lot of environmental, social and governance investing, which is that you=
 shouldn=E2=80=99t invest in socially bad things because eventually they wi=
ll be regulated out of existence. Buying oil-company stock, on this theory,=
 is=C2=A0<em>financially risky</em>, because eventually world governments w=
ill crack down on oil drilling, and the oil companies will not be able to d=
rill for oil profitably in the long run. Eventually a company=E2=80=99s ext=
ernalities =E2=80=94=C2=A0pollution, social harms, etc. =E2=80=94=C2=A0will=
 have to be internalized; shareholders will ultimately have to bear the cos=
ts that the company imposes on society.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I a=
m skeptical about this assumption, without thinking that it matters too muc=
h in practice. I wrote:</p><blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Do you =
think that world governments will come together to ban or limit oil drillin=
g to limit=C2=A0climate change? Do you think governments will regulate Face=
book in a way that harms Facebook, or that users will flee over the most re=
cent controversies? I dunno, maybe, but my tendency is to bet on inaction i=
n these areas.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But does it matter? If all t=
he shareholders of all the oil companies go to them and say =E2=80=9Cfind a=
 way to stop drilling oil because eventually there will be laws against it,=
=E2=80=9D and the oil companies do what the shareholders want and pivot awa=
y from oil, and new oil projects can=E2=80=99t get financed because investo=
rs all think that they are not viable in the long run, then the problem is =
solved,=C2=A0<em>even if governments never actually pass laws against it</e=
m>.=C2=A0</p></blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">On the other hand <a=
 href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/25241118.274768/aHR0=
cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjEtMTAtMDUvd2FsbC1zdHJ=
lZXQtcy1zaGlmdC1zb3V0aC1ydW5zLWludG8tdGV4YXMtZmxvcmlkYS1jdWx0dXJlLXdhcnM/60=
